Key Match Events: Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal in the 80th minute.
Wout Weghorst assisted Memphis Depay's goal to make it 2-2.
Christoph Baumgartner provided the assist for Sabitzer's winning goal.
Alexander Prass registered his second assist in two games.
Donyell Malen scored an own goal for Austria.
Pre-Game Insights: Ralf Rangnick emphasized Austria's chances of beating any team if they made it through the group stage.
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Koeman criticized his team's lack of control and aggression.
Ralf Rangnick praised his team's performance and the depth of his squad.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria will play the runners-up from Group F in the last 16.
Netherlands are guaranteed a place in the knockout stage despite finishing third in their group.
Others: Memphis Depay is now just four goals off the all-time scoring record for the Netherlands with 46 goals.
Ralf Rangnick made four changes to the starting lineup, including resting key players Christoph Baumgartner and Konrad Laimer.
